04/03/2004
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The defence ministry announced Wednesday (3 March) that it has signed a memorandum with the US defence giant Northrop Grumman on the possible establishment of US bases in Romania. Defence Minister Ioan Mircea Pascu explained that the document is part of the technical consultations between Washington and Bucharest on the restructuring of US forces in Europe. US experts have examined facilities in both Romania and Bulgaria.
In other news Wednesday, Prime Minister Adrian Nastase met with President Ion Iliescu to discuss the planned government shuffle and other political issues. Officials have decided to create three new deputy prime minister posts. (AFP, Rompres, Mediafax, BBC - 03/03/04)
